    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-12-24T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-12-24T04:00:00-05:00" n="461"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d461">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/6876: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Mukden</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sokobin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mukden</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-12-24T17:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 24, 1925—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>It is reported that Marshal Chang has completely defeated Kuo.<note n="44"
                        xml:id="d461fn44">Kuo Sung-ling, commander of Manchurian forces attempting
                        to overthrow Chang Tso-lin.</note> Most of the forces of Kuo have
                    surrendered. Kuo fled.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sokobin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
